    "content": {
        "text": "This farm worker is lifting potatoes out of the soil with a fork. For Van Gogh, this painting was an exercise in 'modelling' figures. Having been criticised for the stiff, flat figures in The Potato Eaters, he was trying to give this one a bit more life and volume. The woman's pose is still slightly rigid. The proportions are not quite right either: her head is too small compared to her body, her hands are huge, and her wooden shoes are gigantic. In the sky, there is a tiny hint of blue.",
        "references": []
    }
}

