        "text": "The more you zoom in, the better you can see that Van Gogh used a large network of thin brushstrokes to suggest the forms of the human body. It's almost as if he were drawing in thin paint. You can also see the contrasting colours: green, orange-red and purple. But if you look from a distance (or through your eyelashes), all those colours melt into a warm grey. Van Gogh based the female torso in this painting on one of his favourite plaster casts: a small copy of a classical sculpture of Venus.",
